1. npm init, install mysql and sequelize packages.
2. install sequelize-cli package globally - npm install -g sequelize-cli
3. sequelize init
4. open the config.json in the new config folder, edit in your mysql information (in the development object).
5. create a model
6. create sync for the models (require the models folder, and change the serlisten to do the db sync thing)
7. change the slashes to the correct way in index.js under (var config = .....)
8. YOU ALREADY HAVE TO HAVE THE DATABASE CREATED!!!!!